The paper deals with semidefinite programming relaxations for inference problems, specifically community detection in a distribution of random regular graphs. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the Stochastic Block Model and the Degree Regular Block Model, which are topics in machine learning and statistics, falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses computational complexity and hypothesis testing, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
